            {
              "type": "log",
              "text": "{self.name} kept the find and set the house's best minds to it, against the steward's protest that curiosity has never once balanced a ledger. Perhaps not. But the houses that endure are not always the richest — sometimes they are merely the ones who looked closely at the thing everyone else sold."
            }
          ]
